    "Ruckman, Dr. Peter S_": "Daniel rebukes a king and then lets him commit sacrilege.\n3. Promotion without being faithful.\n3. A suggestive song (it accompanies fornication, adultery, [v_Gal_5_19] and pornography; see Gal. 5:19\u201320; [v_Heb_2_15] Heb. 2:15\u201316).\n3. At a time when there is a real [v_Php_4_19] \u201cneed\u201d (Phil. 4:19).\n3. God, in order to be true (Rom. 3:4), had to save mankind Himself (Gen. 22:8 in the Authorized Version: it is not found in the \u201cDead Rat Otherism\u201d of Bob Jones University). In the case of the sinner, the acceptable time is when \u201cgrace\u201d comes by Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` Christ (not Paul `[char_Paul_Act_13]`), where the \u201ctruth of thy salvation\u201d is Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` Christ Himself (\u201cthe way, the truth and the [v_Jhn_14_6] life,\u201d John `[char_John_Ref]` 14:6), to whom a man must come before God will have [v_Rom_9_15] \u201cmercy\u201d on him (Rom. 9:15)\u2014\u201cmultitude of thy mercy\u201d (vs. 13). 69:14 \u201cDeliver me out of the mire, and let me not sink: let me be delivered from them that hate me, and out of the deep waters. 15 Let not the waterflood overflow me, neither let the deep swallow me up, and let not the pit shut her mouth upon me. 16 Hear me, O LORD; for thy lovingkindness is good: turn unto me according to the multitude of thy tender mercies. 17 And hide not thy face from thy servant; for I am in trouble: hear me speedily. 18 Draw nigh unto my soul, and redeem it: deliver me because of mine enemies. 19 Thou hast known my reproach, and my shame, and my dishonour: mine adversaries are all before thee. 20 Reproach hath broken my heart; and I am full of heaviness: and I looked for some to take pity, but there was none; and for comforters, but I found none. 21 They gave me also gall for my meat; and in my thirst they gave me vinegar to drink.\u201d \u201cHear me, O Lord\u201d (vs. 16) is self-explanatory. \u201cThy lovingkindness is good\u201d is self-explanatory, as is the rest of verse [v_Psa_51_1]",
