    "Warren W. Wiersbe": "How were the lies Abraham and Isaac told about their wives signs of unbelief? How is this true of the lies we tell?\n6. Considering how dysfunctional these family members seem in this passage, why do you suppose God kept working through them?\n6. What do you think it was like to be Leah during the more than twenty years of her marriage? What do you think it was like to be Rachel?\n6. Comment on Tozer\u2019s statement: \u201cThe Lord cannot fully bless a man until he has first conquered him.\u201d"
